question: Tell the origin country of car no.382.
llm_answer: SELECT T3.country FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T2.country = T3.origin WHERE T1.ID = 382
correct_answer: SELECT DISTINCT T2.country FROM production AS T1 INNER JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.country = T2.origin WHERE T1.ID = 382

question: Calculate the percentage of cars that belong to the USA.
llm_answer: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.country = 1 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) FROM data AS T1 INNER JOIN production AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN country AS T3 ON T2.country = T3.origin WHERE T3.country = 'USA'
correct_answer: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.country = 'USA' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) FROM production AS T1 INNER JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.country = T2.origin

question: Calculate the average production rate per year from 1971 to 1980. Among them, name the cars with a weight of fewer than 1800 lbs.
